# ORIG TITLE    The Next Day, from Bowie . 
# ORIG CONTENT  David Bowie has released his first new album in 10 years. It is called The Next Day and the first single off the album was Where Are We Now?” The single references a time when Iggy Pop and David Bowie were both living in Berlin and working at the famous Hansa Studios. “The Stars (Are Out Tonight)” is the second single to be released from the new album, which has already topped the iTunes hit-list in at least 21 countries. The video features Tilda Swinton as David Bowie’s wife. Fans are still waiting to hear whether Bowie will tour to support the album. 
